            . I am a bricklayer. I saw the prisoner on the 10th of June, near a scaffolding, in 
               <persName id="t18280703-144-person866">King-street, Camden-town</persName>
            ; I pursued him, and took this trowel from under his waistcoat.</p>
               <p>JAMES BEAGLEY. I had been at work at that scaffolding, and left at eight o'clock; I left this trowel there, and when I returned the witness had got the prisoner with it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I met a man like a bricklayer - he asked me if I was looking for work - I said Yes, and when we got to Camden-town he said he would go to borrow a trowel - he went and got one, gave it me, and told me to go on.</p>
